div.head: Poetic Edda (Excerpt)
div.p: "[Grimnir]'Ratatoskr is the name of the squirrel which must run|in the ash of Yggdrasill;|an eagle’s words he must bring from above|and speak them to Niðhǫggr beneath.'"

div.head: Prose Edda (Excerpt)
div.p: "Then said Ganglere:Ganglere (or Gangleri) is also a name used by Odin when in disguise. This can not be Odin, however, as this Ganglere is talking to Har (or Hár), which is another name used by Odin. What other remarkable things are there to be said about the ash? Har answered: Much is to be said about it. On one of the boughs of the ash sits an eagle, who knows many things. Between his eyes sits a hawk that is called Vedfolner. A squirrel, by name Ratatosk, springs up and down the tree, and carries words of envy between the eagle and Nidhug."
